{"parse":{"title":"Howe Bridge Mines Rescue Station","pageid":30932942,"revid":812906021,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Mines_rescue_gear_and_Howe_Bridge_certificate.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e6/Mines_rescue_gear_and_Howe_Bridge_certificate.JPG/220px-Mines_rescue_gear_and_Howe_Bridge_certificate.JPG\" width=\"220\" height=\"133\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e6/Mines_rescue_gear_and_Howe_Bridge_certificate.JPG/330px-Mines_rescue_gear_and_Howe_Bridge_certificate.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e6/Mines_rescue_gear_and_Howe_Bridge_certificate.JPG/440px-Mines_rescue_gear_and_Howe_Bridge_certificate.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"2920\" data-file-height=\"1767\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Mines_rescue_gear_and_Howe_Bridge_certificate.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Mines rescue gear and Howe Bridge certificate</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Howe Bridge Mines Rescue Station</b> was the first <a href=\"/wiki/Mine_rescue\" title=\"Mine rescue\">mines rescue</a> station on the <a href=\"/wiki/Lancashire_Coalfield\" title=\"Lancashire Coalfield\">Lancashire Coalfield</a> opened\nin 1908 in <a href=\"/wiki/Howe_Bridge\" title=\"Howe Bridge\">Howe Bridge</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Atherton,_Greater_Manchester\" title=\"Atherton, Greater Manchester\">Atherton</a>, then in the <a href=\"/wiki/Historic_counties_of_England\" title=\"Historic counties of England\">historic county</a> of Lancashire, England.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Before Britain's first mines rescue station opened at <a href=\"/wiki/Tankersley,_South_Yorkshire\" title=\"Tankersley, South Yorkshire\">Tankersley</a> in Yorkshire in 1902, pit managers and volunteers were usually the first untrained mines rescuers. They fought fires, rescued victims and recovered bodies in the collieries in which they worked. Rescue stations were recommended in a <a href=\"/wiki/Royal_Commission\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Royal Commission\">Royal Commission</a> in 1886 but were not compulsory until after the 1911 Coal Mines Act was passed. In 1906 the Lancashire and Cheshire Coal Owners Association formed a committee which decided to provide a mines rescue station in Lovers Lane Atherton. \n</p><p>The first rescuers were provided with <a href=\"/wiki/Siebe_Gorman_Proto\" title=\"Siebe Gorman Proto\">Siebe Gorman Proto</a> breathing apparatus which was selected by competition.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> A team from the rescue station was tasked with training rescue teams from each colliery, and provided emergency assistance to collieries throughout the <a href=\"/wiki/Lancashire_Coalfield\" title=\"Lancashire Coalfield\">Lancashire Coalfield</a>.\n</p><p>Teams from the rescue station attended disasters at the Maypole Colliery in <a href=\"/wiki/Abram,_Greater_Manchester\" title=\"Abram, Greater Manchester\">Abram</a> in 1908 and the <a href=\"/wiki/Pretoria_Pit_Disaster\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pretoria Pit Disaster\">Pretoria Pit Disaster</a> in 1910.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>The station closed in 1934 when <a href=\"/wiki/Boothstown_Mines_Rescue_Station\" title=\"Boothstown Mines Rescue Station\">Boothstown Mines Rescue Station</a>, the central rescue station for the coalfield, became operative.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Howe_Bridge_Mines_Rescue_Station&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/List_of_mining_disasters_in_Lancashire\" title=\"List of mining disasters in Lancashire\">List of mining disasters in Lancashire</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Howe_Bridge_Mines_Rescue_Station&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.healeyhero.co.uk/rescue/rescue_hist/pre1911b.htm\"><i>The First Rescue Stations In The Country</i></a>, Healey Hero<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">, retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2011-02-19</span></span></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+First+Rescue+Stations+In+The+Country&amp;rft.pub=Healey+Hero&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.healeyhero.co.uk%2Frescue%2Frescue_hist%2Fpre1911b.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHowe+Bridge+Mines+Rescue+Station\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFDavies2009\">Davies 2009</a>, p.&#160;133</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation\"><a rel